SAVING THROWS AND EFFECTS


SAVING THROWS VS
fear - results in immobilization(terrified), memory loss, unconsiousness,
compliant, concentration loss

depression - results in fuge, concentration loss, disassocation, catatonia

confusion - all of the below. this is the one to be avoided at all costs. 
maxims help here. 

domination
shock
doubt
euphoria

EFFECTS
memory loss
concentration loss
unconsiousness
disocciation
fugue
immobilization
	terrified
	catatonic depression
	catatonic confusion (resulting from confusion, shock, and doubt attacks)
mind-controlled / suggestable / compliant
trauma
PTSD
insanity
mania
psychosomatic affects


